			<p> 

					On a Friday morning in November at the 96th street New York Public Library, the second floor is crowded with strollers at the doorway and the squeals of children. The children are participating in one of the library’s many popular programs, Toy Time.

					<br>
					<br>
					Since the pandemic, New York Libraries, which includes Brooklyn Public Library (BPL), New York Public Library (NYPL), and Queens Public Library (QPL), have seen major growth, with program and library attendance the highest it has been in the last five years.
			</p>
			<p>
			“Brooklyn Public Library is one of the most democratic institutions in the borough and increasingly an important third space,” said Fritzi Bodenheimer, press officer for the Brooklyn Public Library. “Everyone is welcome here. You can come and spend all day without ever having to buy something.”
			</p>
			

			<p>According to data reports from The Libraries, the New York Public Library’s attendance has more than doubled since 2021. 
			</p>

